It is necessary to add that the existing gold-dwelling agreements no longer change, the restriction only concerns new contracts, which should be a further incentive to participate in the programme.
"This is the first case in American history where there will be legal restrictions on the remuneration of general directors," commented the Chairman of the Committee on Financial Services of the House of Representatives, Democrat Barney Frank.
